for%20founders%20in%20tech%20and%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20primarily%20with%20US%20clients%20and%20have%20visited%20the%20US%20several%20times%20in%20the%20past%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20time%20I%20spend%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20more%20I%20realize%20how%20differently%20British%20people%20approach%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20find%20Americans%20to%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20embrace%20challenges%20and%20to%20have%20a%20greater%20appreciation%20for%20risk%2C%20whereas%20British%20people%20prioritize%20comfort%20and%20perfection.%20Here%20are%20the%20main%20traits%20that%20made%20our%20differences%20in%20work%20culture%20most%20apparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb95b41e-c773-4716-ba15-39a2c23f581f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Embracing%20'schlep%20blindness'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.paulgraham.com%2Fschlep.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESchlep%20blindness%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20was%20coined%20by%20the%20Y%20Combinator%20cofounder%20Paul%20Graham.%20It%20means%20we%20can%20tune%20out%20tedious%20tasks%20rather%20than%20try%20to%20tackle%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20Americans%20will%20take%20on%20unglamorous%20problems%2C%20whereas%20Brits%20are%20more%20realistic%20about%20flaws%20and%20hurdles.%20The%20latter%20approach%20can%20make%20you%20realize%20how%20hard%20a%20goal%20is%20to%20achieve%20and%20less%20likely%20to%20take%20on%20a%20new%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20American%20founder%20recently%20told%20me%20starting%20something%20with%20a%20level%20of%20naivety%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20thing%20seems%20tedious%2C%20means%20you'll%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20ignore%20any%20challenges%20and%20just%20get%20on%20with%20it.%20On%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bschlep%2C%26quot%3B%20there's%20often%20a%20higher%20reward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20this%20is%20because%20there%20is%20a%20stronger%20entrepreneurial%20and%20meritocratic%20spirit%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20my%20British%20friends%20talk%20about%20changing%20careers%20to%20something%20more%20fulfilling%20that%20aligns%20with%20their%20passions.%20But%20people%20I've%20talked%20to%20in%20the%20US%20have%20said%20it's%20more%20important%20to%20become%20passionate%20about%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20shouldn't%20hate%20your%20job%2C%20but%20incremental%20work%20that%20seems%20boring%20is%20often%20building%20toward%20a%20higher%20return%20on%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20my%20ghostwriting%20business%2C%20it%20took%20months%20of%20rejection%20to%20get%20my%20first%20client.%20If%20I'd%20known%20how%20hard%20it%20would%20be%2C%20I%20might%20never%20have%20started.%20Instead%2C%20I%20just%20took%20it%20one%20day%20at%20a%20time%20and%20got%20used%20to%20doing%20uncomfortable%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221fb17709-bb7d-432f-bb52-36df71109d01%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Intentional%20network%20building%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Britain%2C%20our%20social%20and%20professional%20circles%20often%20form%20through%20chance%20%E2%80%94%20school%20connections%2C%20family%20friends%2C%20or%20colleagues.%20Most%20of%20my%20school%20friends%20still%20live%20and%20network%20in%20the%20same%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Americans%20I've%20met%20are%20more%20intentional%20about%20their%20circle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20founders%20and%20businesspeople%20I%20met%20in%20the%20US%20have%20built%20reaching%20out%20to%20interesting%20people%20online%20into%20their%20daily%20schedules.%20They've%20found%20friends%2C%20cofounders%2C%20and%20opportunities%20from%20online%20networking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20it's%20the%20fear%20of%20failure%20or%20tall-poppy%20syndrome%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20that%20people%20aren't%20as%20proactive%20about%20networking%20in%20the%20UK.%20Brits%20sometimes%20view%20Americans%20as%20obnoxious%2C%20but%20I%20see%20it%20as%20being%20unapologetic%20and%20ambitious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20always%20found%20it%20easier%20to%20build%20relationships%20across%20the%20pond.%20I%20think%20alongside%20being%20intentional%2C%20there's%20also%20more%20openness%20and%20high%20energy%20toward%20socializing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20London%2C%20it's%20an%20unwritten%20rule%20that%20you%20don't%20talk%20to%20strangers.%20In%20America%2C%20you%20walk%20into%20a%20clothing%20store%20and%20feel%20as%20if%20the%20clerk%20is%20your%20best%20friend%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20goes%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20engage%20in%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22064082d3-19ec-4f01-871a-33be4d29864d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Execution%20over%20perfection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDone%20beats%20perfect%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20saying%20I%20often%20hear%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Britain%2C%20we%20often%20delay%20launching%20a%20product%20or%20idea%20until%20everything%20is%20polished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20this%20is%20partly%20because%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bstiff%20upper%20lip%26quot%3B%20stereotype.%20To%20fail%20at%20something%20would%20be%20to%20show%20emotion%2C%20which%20can%20be%20viewed%20negatively%20in%20British%20culture.%20Perfectionism%20is%20often%20fear%20in%20disguise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20States%2C%20emails%20are%20answered%20within%20hours.%20Problems%20are%20solved%20that%20day.%20My%20American%20friends%20do%20everything%20with%20another%20level%20of%20intensity.%20Before%20they%20even%20have%20time%20to%20think%2C%20they've%20taken%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20that%20we%20should%20take%20our%20time%20when%20deciding%20on%20the%20big%20things%20like%20what%20to%20work%20on%20and%20whom%20to%20partner%20with.%20But%20once%20you're%20on%20the%20right%20path%2C%20the%20quicker%20you%20can%20run%20experiments%20to%20get%20feedback%2C%20the%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20spend%20hours%20sweating%20over%20tiny%20details%20in%20both%20my%20work%20and%20my%20personal%20life.%20It%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20practice%2C%20but%20eventually%20I%20learned%20to%20set%20deadlines%2C%20ignore%20the%20internal%20British%20voice%2C%20and%20start%20taking%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEach%20iteration%20would%20get%20me%20to%20where%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20far%20quicker%20than%20trying%20to%20be%20perfect%20before%20launching.%20I%20think%20is%20more%20common%20in%20British%20culture%20where%20not%20trying%20at%20all%20is%20better%20than%20trying%20and%20failing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22583ac0de-a54b-4b06-99cc-18b74942abeb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Relationship%20with%20challenge%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20entrepreneurs%20I've%20met%20seem%20to%20have%20a%20different%20approach%20to%20difficulty%20itself.%20They%20actively%20seek%20out%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20got%20back%20from%20a%20trip%20to%20New%20York%20where%20I%20met%20a%20bunch%20of%20founders.%20We%20went%20for%20a%20run%20and%20chatted%20about%20business%20and%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20pattern%20where%20the%20serious%20marathon%20runners%20were%20also%20successful%20in%20work.%20They%20said%20how%20they%20loved%20embracing%20pain%20and%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%2C%20like%20marathons%2C%20are%20hard%20to%20run%2C%20and%20it%20takes%20a%20certain%20type%20to%20seek%20out%20that%20challenge.%20I'm%20not%20saying%20everyone%20in%20the%20US%20is%20like%20this%2C%20but%20I%20came%20across%20a%20lot%20who%20seemed%20to%20thrive%20in%20challenging%2C%20chaotic%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20UK%2C%20it's%20more%20normal%20to%20strive%20for%20comfort%3A%20a%20respectable%20house%20and%20reasonable%20working%20hours.%20It%20may%20be%20because%20British%20culture%20doesn't%20glamourize%20ambition%20to%20the%20same%20extent%20as%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20I%20find%20myself%20wishing%20for%20a%20chilled%20weekend.%20As%20soon%20as%20I%20get%20one%2C%20my%20mind%20craves%20the%20rush%20of%20building%20things.%20This%20mindset%20makes%20me%20feel%20a%20little%20out%20of%20place%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20meet%20a%20lot%20of%20British%20people%20who%20don't%20enjoy%20their%20work%20or%20like%20to%20talk%20about%20it.%20Whereas%2C%20when%20I%20see%20people%20in%20WeWork%20at%20the%20weekend%2C%20I%20love%20it.%20It%20tells%20me%20we've%20got%20something%20in%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e6793917-5cb9-49ae-9082-80b3f033a4d8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20different%20game%20entirely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20work%2C%20British%20and%20American%20cultures%20aren't%20playing%20the%20same%20game%20with%20different%20results%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20playing%20different%20games%20with%20different%20rules%20and%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBritish%20culture%20optimizes%20for%20stability%2C%20respectability%2C%20and%20manageable%20progress.%20American%20entrepreneurial%20culture%20optimizes%20for%20outsize%20impact%2C%20rapid%20evolution%2C%20and%20breakthrough%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20approach%20is%20inherently%20superior%2C%20but%20they%20produce%20different%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20my%20part%2C%20these%20insights%20have%20transformed%20how%20I%20build%20my%20business.%20I've%20started%20embracing%20unglamorous%20challenges%2C%20setting%20more%20ambitious%20targets%2C%20launching%20faster%2C%20and%20viewing%20difficulties%20as%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-vs-uk-work-culture-american-clients-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743500805000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67eadffc69253ccddf9ac970%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-vs-uk-work-culture-american-clients-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20British%20ghostwriter%20who%20works%20with%20US%20clients%20found%20t