20a%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EAnts%20work%20from%20home%20(yours%2C%20that%20is)%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnts%20owe%20much%20of%20their%20success%20to%20their%20highly%20social%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20colony%2C%20some%20individuals%20(female%20queens%20and%20male%20drones)%20are%20responsible%20for%20reproduction%2C%20while%20others%20(workers)%20are%20busy%20caring%20for%20the%20young%2C%20cleaning%20or%20foraging%20for%20food.%20Workers%20ants%20are%20always%20female.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnt%20colonies%20do%20not%20have%20leaders.%20They%20are%20an%20excellent%20example%20of%20collective%20behaviour%20and%20swarm%20intelligence%2C%20where%20individuals%20following%20relatively%20simple%20rules%20can%20collectively%20achieve%20far%20more%20than%20any%20individual%20could%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20the%20individual%20neurons%20in%20your%20brain%20can't%20compose%20music%2C%20play%20football%2C%20or%20read%20articles%2C%20the%20brain%20as%20a%20whole%20can%20achieve%20all%20these%20feats%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EColonies%20of%20co-operating%20ants%20are%20capable%20of%20amazingly%20sophisticated%20behaviours%20such%20as%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Ebuilding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fbeheco%2Farticle-abstract%2F26%2F1%2F223%2F2262407%3FredirectedFrom%3Dfulltext%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eefficient%20trail%20networks%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3Ebuilding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.princeton.edu%2Fnews%2F2015%2F11%2F30%2Fants-build-living-bridges-their-bodies-speak-volumes-about-group-intelligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20bridges%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20their%20bodies%2C%20and%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%26quot%3Bfarming%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.adn7179%5C%22%20target%3D%5