20mates%20to%20any%20food%20it%20finds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnts%20may%20also%20come%20inside%20in%20search%20of%20water%2C%20particularly%20when%20the%20weather%20is%20hot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20species%20prefer%20to%20build%20their%20nests%20in%20humid%20environments%2C%20which%20might%20explain%20why%20they%20are%20often%20found%20in%20bathrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20once%20discovered%20an%20entire%20colony%20of%20sugar%20ants%20nesting%20inside%20my%20aquarium%20filter!%20The%20combination%20of%20high%20humidity%20and%20an%20enclosed%20structure%20made%20it%20an%20ideal%20place%20to%20build%20a%20nest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20heavy%20rains%20can%20flood%20ant%20nests%2C%20prompting%20colonies%20to%20seek%20drier%20ground%20-%20sometimes%20leading%20them%20straight%20into%20our%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EI%20live%20in%20an%20upper-floor%20apartment.%20How%20did%20ants%20get%20in%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20ant%20species%20are%20exceptional%20climbers%2C%20thanks%20to%20tiny%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0141269%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadhesive%3C%2Fa%3E%20pads%20and%20fine%20hairs%20on%20their%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20specialised%20structures%20allow%20ants%20to%20stick%20to%20walls%20and%20find%20footholds%20even%20on%20surfaces%20that%20appear%20smooth%20to%20the%20human%20eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarkably%2C%20some%20canopy-dwelling%20ants%20have%20evolved%20a%20behaviour%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0141269%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtrolled%20descent%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20which%20protects%20them%20when%20they%20fall.%20By%20adjusting%20the%20position%20of%20their%20abdomens%2C%20falling%20ants%20can%20steer%20their%20trajectory%2C%20di